                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td bgcolor="#000000" height="8" width="100%" colspan="3"><span class="header">STCCG Puzzule Two: Klingon Beat Up On</span></td></tr><tr><td bgcolor="#333399" height="2" width="41%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="1%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="58%" bgcolor="#FF9C00"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td></tr></table><TABLE WIDTH="100%" CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN=2><SPAN CLASS="header">Rating </SPAN><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/rating/9.gif" BORDER=0></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=48"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=48"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=5866">Franklin "LooPHolE" Kenter</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Description</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%"><span class=text>Puzzles gives players a chance to learn though applying their knowlegde with their Strategema, Vulcan Logic, and Klingon Honor</span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Article</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%" ><span class=text>If you do not like the idea of puzzles, INGORE them. If you wish not to participate, please do not. Then, you will not waste you time with them.<br>
<br>
If you do not beleive puzzles are not articles, I beg to differ. Although puzzles do not directly enhance one’s technique or ability, they force people to think. As a result, players will learn new idea just like normal articles do. They are an indirect form of teaching as opposed to a direct form of teaching from normal. If  you slam my article and continue to do so (for no reason), do not be surprised if I do the same to you (I am talking about those who are giving it a 1 for no reason). There is no reason for you to slam my article simply because it is a change of pace. Those who are trying and enjoying it, are thinking hard and finding creative (if not the right) answers; those who are not, tend not to care and do not try a whole lot (if not all). I am sorry if I put up a new, creative and innovative thing, but is that not the idea?<br>
<br>
<br>
ANSWER TO PUZZLE ONE (*denotes key cards to solution):<br>
<br>
Princess placed numberous Borg Queens (12 or more) in her discard pile. After having all of you personnel killed off, you decided to use your *Persistence of Memory* you earn from solving your one mission on your *Anti-Time Anomaly*. As a result, the Anti-Time Anomaly is reversed, and all personnel in the discard pile are immediately placed into play “anywhere” regardless of uniqueness (including the Borg Queen). Princess is then able to use her twelve (or more) Borg Queens that were discarded to pass Founder Secret. Nifty trick!<br>
<br>
She uses *The Emperor’s New Cloak* to steal the artifacts to steal the artifacts (which actually count as equpiment too) that past Founder Secret.<br>
<br>
I liked the Devidan Forgers solution too; however, Mask of Gorgano does not affect dead people. She uses one Borg Queen, plays *Devidan Forgers*. You have two Mr. Spocks in your discard pile, and thus adding 20 CUNNING to Borg Queen. Queen now has 32 CUNNING. She plays the *Eyes in the Dark*, if she&#146;s lucky she&#146;ll have 41 or more CUNNING. Add a *Any tricorder* and she&#146;ll pass founder secret. I never thought of that!<br>
<br>
Puzzle Number Two: Klingon Beat Up On<br>
<br>
DIFFICULTY: Question on the Academy Entrance Exam (Medium-Hard)<br>
CARD KNOWLEDGE	<br>
<br>
<br>
Your Opponent<br>
<br>
Name: Pu Uoy Taeb<br>
Affiliation: Federation/Klingon/(Non-aligned)<br>
Rating: 1620<br>
Deck Information: Seeds Treaty:Federation/Klingon with Open Diplomatic Relations<br>
Seeds all Federation facilities<br>
Does not use The Devil or personnel with CUNNING&lt;8<br>
<br>
You<br>
<br>
Name: Loophole<br>
Affiliation: Federation/Klingon/(Non-aligned)<br>
Rating: 1572<br>
Deck Information: Only Personnel and Ships in draw deck<br>
Seeds Treaty:Federation/Klingon with Open Diplomatic Relations <br>
Seeds and uses three side decks<br>
Do not use Storage Compartment Door or The Devil<br>
<br>
Current Situation:<br>
You have your only eight personnel alive on a Yiridian Shuttle. Four of those personnel are Kor, Kang, Kolath, and Jadiza Dax so you can solve A Good Day to Live. Pu Uoy Teab has a Federation (with Captain Kirk) ship, three Klingon ships, and two Non-Aligned ships each with WEAPONS&gt;14 that can attack your Yridian Shuttle this turn (all staffed with a matching leader). You nor the opponent have no cards in hand, no hidden aganedas, events or incidents on the table. The opponent moves each ship and attacks with each one seperately. Amazingly, you realize that your Yridian Shuttle is not doomed and remains on the table, but only in this special circumstance.<br>
<br>
Who are those four other people?<br>
<br>
Post your answers when you rate this puzzle; answer(s) will be posted on the next puzzle.<br>
<br>
Questions?<br>
Dmail me.<br>
<br>
Next Puzzle: Six Days...<br>
